race.comment: MR BANNOCK (2) has been nudged out both starts this preparation and his latest over 1800m on the Hillside in stronger caught the eye. Has an awkward barrier but rates strongly and the step up to 2000m is ideal. CONVO (10) peaks for Ciaron Maher and is busting to win. Placed in a 66 this trip at Cranbourne last time and can fight out the finish with average luck in the run. CROSSOVERKID (6) resumed over a mile at Cranbourne and just missed as favourite. He's been kept on the fresh side and has placed 2/3 this distance and 3/3 second-up. Has more to give and the winkers go on again. A chance. Including MICKIDABEEL (1) at a price. Did a big job to deliver a Werribee Maiden over a mile and will be fitter. This is a lot harder but he will enjoy a soft run and will win more races.
